98. incolumis . . . in urbe, in· stead of losing his citizenship and being exiled, as he would have been if convicted.

100. nigrae sucus loliginis, i.e. the essence of black malignity. The figure is from the excretion of the cuttlefish from which India ink is made. Cf. hic niger est, v. 85.

101. aerugo mera, pure verdi- gris: comparing slander to rust eating into bronze, etc., which rust appears to do. Cf. A. P. 330.
